  <bioghist id="aspace_9755cc00cb2f30e6dcd1a0a9c7aa494a">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>Starting in 1995, the Dean of Students' Office of Student Support had a staff person providing support for lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender (LGBT) students and students questioning or dealing with their sexual or gender identity. This unit offered peer counseling programs, peer-led support groups, and relevant events and programming. In the spring of 1999, Dean of Students staff brought the student-led support groups together under an administrative umbrella called Haven. An online peer mentoring service, faQ, was started in spring 2006.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_24b234a2e0491dc09be27b12d27b04e5">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Clippings, handouts, and posters and some email, correspondence, administrative files from LBGT Support and Haven, 1979-2007. Foam-core panel with introduction to Spring 2006 exhibit at Tatkon Center.</p>  </scopecontent>
